Warehouse Manager
Morgan McKinley
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 5 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Morgan McKinley is currently working with a well know regional logistics and warehousing company who is seeking a Warehouse Manager to oversee all warehouse operations such as receiving, inspection, quality control, Invoice approval, shipping and delivery. Our client works with multinational companies supporting their distribution and warehousing requirements throughout the GCC.
The Warehouse Manager will be responsible for all warehouse primary functions such as inbound, outbound, storage and inventory management. This will include managing the warehousing operations and ensuring that all operational objectives are met taking into account quality, quantity and cost through development and execution of tactical and operational initiatives.
REQUIREMENTS
Essential:
- Diploma in Warehousing and Distribution and Materials management
- 5 years experience in supply chain functions; planning, procurement, warehousing and transportation
- Ability to work effectively in a multicultural team environment and motivate team members
- Excellent Microsoft computer skills ( excel)
Skills:
- Strong leadership qualities
- Oracle Inventory Management Module
- Communication and Organization skills
ABOUT THE COMPANY
